google_info: Dr. Yaser Bakkar, CMP - Career Development Consultant ...
name: Dr. Yaser Bakkar, CMP
information: Career Development Specialist | Trainer & Coach | Podcaster | Inspiring people to find their calling
location: Saudi Arabia Contact info
about: I started my career as a psychiatrist, who treats psychologically ill people. I discovered that not all how suffer from psychological challenges are sick, some of them just lost their way, they can't find answers to the most challenging questions such as: What am I Meant To Do? Which is the right field that I will flourish in if I spend my time, effort and energy in? Although, it is a long journey to figure that out, but when anyone starts it by the right way and the right tool, he or she will live differently, and this is what I committed my life to.Based on solid experience in Career Counseling and Development over the last 9 years, I founded (IKTSHAF)(www.iktshaf.com) as the largest Arabic platform to help youth to find their career way after high school with more than 100,000 subscribers.In the last year, I developed the first Arabic certification in Career Counseling for youth (CCY). This certification dedicated to developing career counseling skills for youth workers. It will empower them to provide guidance to youth about their career life after high schools. You can learn more about it at (www.ccytrainin.com)Currently, I am working on developing the largest Arabic Career Counseling platform for all age groups.My main training courses I teach are: - How to choose a college major? (for high school students)- What should you do now to get a job after graduation? (for university students)- How to choose and build fulfilling career?- Career Counseling skills for youth worker (as a part of CCY certificate) MY main competencies are: - Career assessment for individuals by using Strong interest Inventory (SII), MBTI, Clifton StrengthsFinder, and other tools- Career Training and Coaching for different age groups- Building and running platforms in Career Counseling My MBTI type is ENTP.My top talent themes are:- Input - Ideation - Futuristic - Learner - Intellection … see more
